    "created_at": "2014-05-29T17:02:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-05-29T17:02:16Z",
    "body": "I don't think that leaking resources is the best default, but having a by-value close operation that explicitly leaks the library would be more ok.\n\nThis is a very low-level implementation of a dynamic plugin, and I think its functions are `unsafe` for good reasons.\n",
